  "measurement_note": "Size is s, both the array length and query count. Every array value is 1 and every query is [0,1], so each answer is s. Grouping the shared small step and building one reverse DP takes O(s) on this workload and lies within the required O((n+q)sqrt(n)) class. Independently caching the progression for the repeated step has the same behavior. Traversing the full array separately for every query takes O(s^2), completes all 16/64/256 tiers, and is rejected only by scaling.",
